\f0\fs24 \cf0 # Element Visual Language Bible\
**Version:** 1.0\
**Project:** Card Game\
**Purpose:** Canonical visual reference for Leonardo AI, Claude Code, artists, and future asset generation.\
\
---\
\
# Overview\
\
Every element in the game should have a unique visual language.\
\
An element is **not simply a color**.\
\
Each one should communicate:\
\
- personality\
- emotion\
- movement\
- materials\
- lighting\
- texture\
- age\
- energy\
- atmosphere\
- symbolism\
\
This document exists so generated artwork remains visually diverse and avoids every element becoming "glowing colored magic."\
\
---\
\
# Standard Element Template\
\
Each element should define:\
\
## Theme\
\
The emotional identity of the element.\
\
## Primary Colors\
\
Dominant colors.\
\
## Secondary Colors\
\
Supporting colors.\
\
## Accent Colors\
\
Small highlight colors.\
\
## Materials\
\
Physical materials associated with the element.\
\
## Textures\
\
Surface detail.\
\
## Lighting\
\
How light behaves.\
\
## Motion\
\
How the energy moves.\
\
## Shapes\
\
Common forms.\
\
## Layering\
\
Visual construction order.\
\
## Atmosphere\
\
Environmental effects.\
\
## Symbolism\
\
Concepts represented.\
\
## Negative Associations\
\
Things Leonardo commonly overuses that should be avoided.\
\
