\
# Element Combination Rules\
\
Elements should blend naturally.\
\
## Fire + Nature\
\
Use:\
\
- Burning vines\
- Charred bark\
- Embers\
- Ash-covered roots\
\
Avoid:\
\
- Green fire\
\
---\
\
## Fire + Metal\
\
Use:\
\
- Molten steel\
- Heated armor\
- Forge sparks\
- Liquid iron\
\
Avoid:\
\
- Simply painting metal red\
\
---\
\
## Water + Nature\
\
Use:\
\
- Wet moss\
- Lotus flowers\
- River roots\
- Lily pads\
- Mist\
\
Avoid:\
\
- Blue leaves\
\
---\
\
## Ice + Shadow\
\
Use:\
\
- Black frost\
- Frozen mist\
- Obsidian crystals\
- Dark glaciers\
\
Avoid:\
\
- Black snow\
\
---\
\
## Lightning + Metal\
\
Use:\
\
- Charged armor\
- Tesla coils\
- Ionized steel\
- Electric engravings\
\
Avoid:\
\
- Yellow glowing swords\
\
---\
\
# Final Principle\
\
Every element should be recognizable **even without color**.\
\
A player should identify an element by:\
\
- silhouette\
- materials\
- lighting\
- motion\
- textures\
- atmosphere\
\
Color should reinforce an element\'97not define it.}